replies.body:
@Anyael

You say that you like the deceptive nature of her playstyle. Whittling an enemy down with poison, slowly killing them before they can notice, then going in for the kill when it was too late for them to escape. You don't seem to understand that that was the **entire** premise of the Old Cassiopeia. I also absolutely loved this playstyle. It was subtle, sneaky and exciting. A perfect fit for a champion who uses her wits and wiles to get ahead.

This new Cassiopeia completely scraps that ideal. There is no subtleness, no deception; just 'land poison, slam face on E until dead.' It is not fun or creative in the slightest. She no longer requires the patience and cunning that old Cass did, just spam Twin Fangs and hope you win.
